column1: Contents: UV-visible absorbance data from West Antarctic seawater samples, acquired on Thermo Evolution 300 Spectrophotometer at 0.1 nm increments
Measurements made on aliquots from PAL1314 and LMG1401 water samples preserved for DOC analysis (GF/F filtered to 0.7 um nominal)
XXX: Sequential number assigned arbitrarily on date of analysis
YYYYYY: Origin of sample; PAL1314 (Palmer Station 2013-2014 field season or LMG1401 (collected on PAL-LTER cruise aboard Laurence M. Gould)
ZZZZZZ: Sample ID assigned from PAL1314 or LMG1401 (consult applicable DOC sample log)
AAAA: Matrix used in spectrophotometer reference cell: 0.2 um oligotrophic filtered seawater from 50 m at the Bermuda-Atlantic Time Series station, or RSMAS standard reference low carbon water
